-- Cotton Traders May Have Reneged on 20% of Contracts, WSJ Says
-- B y   C l a u d i a   C a r p e n t e r
-- 2012-08-31T05:58:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-31/cotton-traders-may-have-reneged-on-20-of-contracts-wsj-says.html
Cotton traders may have reneged on
or rewritten 20 percent of contracts since 2010, worth as much
as $12 billion, the Wall Street Journal said, citing Terry Townsend, executive director of the  International Cotton
Advisory Committee .  Cotton growers and textile mills walked away from supply
agreements after prices turned against them, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
